LTV Corp said it has received a contractworth more than 500 mln dlrs from Boeing Co to produce majorsections for Boeing 767, 757 and 747 airliners, including thenew 747-400.    The company said the contract covers continuing productionthrough mid-1990.  LTV makes aft body sections and horizontaland vertical stabilizers for 747 and 757's and horizontalstabilizers for 767's.    It said as part of the contract it will build a new type ofhorizontal stabilizer for the 747-400 containing tanks capableof holding 3,300 gallons of fuel.    The added fuel capacity will allow the 747-400 to fly about1,000 miles further than the 747-300, LTV said.    The company said it will start making the 747-400 shipsetsin June and the first aircraft is scheduled for completion inearly 1988.  It is to be delivered to NWA Inc &lt;NWA> in December1988. Reuter&#3;